<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>About BenchWalaAI</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/about.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>
    <div class="page-container">
      <div class="page-header">
        <h1>About BenchWalaAI</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="intro-section">
        <p>
          BenchWalaAI is a centralized exam management platform designed to
          solve real exam-day problems like seat confusion, attendance tracking,
          staff allocation, and booklet shortages.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="workflow-section">
        <h3>How the System Works</h3>
        <ul class="workflow-list">
          <li class="workflow-item">
            <strong>Global Admin</strong> creates exams and assigns departments.
          </li>
          <li class="workflow-item">
            <strong>Local Admin</strong> uploads classrooms, students, and staff
            using CSV files.
          </li>
          <li class="workflow-item">
            Seats are <strong>automatically allocated</strong> based on
            available benches.
          </li>
          <li class="workflow-item">
            Staff is <strong>auto-assigned</strong> to classrooms.
          </li>
          <li class="workflow-item">
            Students log in to see their
            <strong>classroom and bench number</strong>.
          </li>
          <li class="workflow-item">
            Staff marks <strong>attendance</strong> and enters
            <strong>booklet count</strong>.
          </li>
          <li class="workflow-item">
            Global Admin monitors
            <strong>attendance and booklet shortages</strong> live.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="access-section">
        <h3>Who Can Access</h3>
        <ul class="access-list">
          <li>Admins – via manual account creation</li>
          <li>Staff – via CSV upload</li>
          <li>Students – via CSV upload</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="closing">
        <p>
          This system minimizes manual errors and ensures smooth, transparent
          exam execution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
